    "description_long": "This is a large, pole-mounted traffic light assembly designed for urban intersections. The structure consists of a tall, vertical cylindrical pole supporting two long, curved horizontal arms that extend over a roadway. Attached to the arms are two sets of traffic signal lights, each with three distinct lenses, likely for red, yellow, and green signals. There is also a small surveillance or sensor device mounted above the main arm, and a control box is affixed to the pole. The entire assembly is constructed primarily from dark-colored metal, with the signal lights and control box featuring some weathered, brownish accents.",
